  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\ncurrently \r\n\r\nthe rpc endpoints table only supports the URL\r\n\r\n```\r\n[rpc_endpoints]\r\noptimism = \"https://example.com/\"\r\nmainnet = \"${_CONFIG_MAINNET}\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nwe should also make it possible to configure:\r\n* retry_backoff\r\n* retries\r\n* compute_units_per_second\r\n\r\n\r\nSee also:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/fdad9fb0dde45d3476fc5d1fe6f40e8dc7c17caa/crates/evm/core/src/opts.rs#L26-L38\r\n\r\n## TODO \r\nadd a new type that has all these fields (`RpcEndpointConfig`) with custom serialize, deserialize so it is backwards compatible with (Deserialize from String gets interpreted as `RpcEndpoint`, object as `RpcEndpointConfig`):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/fdad9fb0dde45d3476fc5d1fe6f40e8dc7c17caa/crates/config/src/endpoints.rs#L15-L15\r\nref \r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/4958\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
